The paper discusses the problem of designing channel access architectures for wireless nodes, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a practical solution using sparse-graph based coding scheme and belief-propagation decoder, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the relevance of the proposed solution for 5G/6G, which falls under the category of computer communication (cs.COM).
